<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012070>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Photomicrograph of Corethrella kipferi female head capsule, frontal view. Scale bar = 0.125 mm. Abbreviations: cl = clypeus; cs = coronal suture; fr = frons; f = flagellomeres; p = palpal segments." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012070/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012072>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Photomicrograph of Corethrella kipferi female wing, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012072/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012068>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Photomicrograph of Corethrella kipferi female habitus, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012068/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012074>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Photomicrographs of Corethrella kipferi fourth-instar larval habitus. (a) Dorsal view. (b) Ventral view. (c) Lateral view. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012074/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012076>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Photomicrograph of Corethrella kipferi fourth-instar larval head capsule, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.125 mm. Abbreviations: ant = antenna; gen = gena; lmpo = postmentum; lmpr = prementum; lr = labrum; md = mandible; mx = maxilla." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012076/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012078>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Line drawing of Corethrella kipferi fourth-instar larva, ventral view. Abbreviations: I–VIII, X = numbered abdominal segments; M = mesothorax; P = prothorax; T = metathorax. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012078/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7012080>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Number of Corethrella kipferi larvae captured in hyporheic habitats of Bull Creek. Perennial and ephemeral surface water sites are indicated in blue and red, respectively. Sublocations at the perennial habitat were upstream (circles) and downstream (squares) of a medial gravel bar (triangles), which had ephemeral flow. Peckout Hollow (pluses) was an ephemeral tributary located approximately 2 km downstream of the medial gravel bar." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7012080/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

